"This acts as a very simple vimrc with useful for beginners (without all of the
"personal modifications that not everyone would like). I like to think of this
"as settings that most people would enjoy having. I try not to override any
"defaults. If I were to introduce someone to vim, I'd give them this vimrc,
"rather than my normal one.

"The only special things this does is remap <F9> to saving and compiling (with
"make). It also makes the tab character insert 2 spaces, rather than a tab.
set nocompatible "break away from vi compatibility

set title "show title in console bar
set number " show line numbers
set hls "do highlighting
set ruler
set smartcase
set incsearch "Incremental search
set hlsearch
set showcmd
set cmdheight=2 " avoid 'Press Enter to continue'
set ignorecase
set wildmenu
set showmatch "show matching brackets
syntax on

" Spaces are better than tabs
set autoindent
set smartindent
set expandtab
au BufRead,BufNewFile Makefile set ts=4 sw=4 noexpandtab
set smarttab
set tabstop=2 "Change this line to set how large tabs are
set shiftwidth=2

set bs=indent,eol,start " allow backspacing over everything in insert mode

" Turn off annoying error bells
set noerrorbells
set novisualbell

"Compile with 1 step
set makeprg=make
imap <F9> <Esc><F9>
noremap <F9> <Esc>:wa<Cr>:make<Cr>

"Change Y to make sense
nnoremap Y y$

"Hell yeh paste mode!
au InsertLeave * set nopaste

"File type specific
set wildignore=*.o,*.ui,*.uo,*.exe,.git

"C, C++, Java
autocmd Filetype c,cpp,java set cindent 

